    <note>Shen(2) Lun [1454] Jizong's [1446] father. He originally supported himself by lecturing on the San Li. Later on, as a result of a recommendation, he became attached to the army of Zhao(1) Kuangyin (Taizu) [9001] and was involved in financial affairs. Also known by the mingzi Yilun. XCB, 3.1a, 7.7b, 8.3a; XZZTJ, 2.10b-11a; SHY:SH, 49.3a, 4a; SS, 264.4b-6a; TZHDSL, 42.5b. CBD, 1, 678.</note>
